class Solution {
    public int hammingWeight(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n != 0) {
            count += n & 1;
            n >>>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses bitwise operations to count the number of set bits in the binary representation of n. It iterates through each bit, adding the least significant bit to the count and then shifting n to the right. This approach is efficient as it directly manipulates the bits and does not require any additional data structures.

